{"key":"processedPost-10280267","value":{"id":10280267,"first":10280147,"last":14432493,"when":1241402464,"utime":"05/04/09 05:01 AM","content":"Yes.&nbsp; If your grains are at the correct moisture content, the verm will pull moisture from them.&nbsp; In the early days it was common for growers to drop some verm in the grain jars to soak up excess moisture.&nbsp; However, if you follow a proper <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Grain-Preparation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">grain tek</a>, your grains won't be too wet.<br /><br />About the only real use for verm in grain jars is if you plan to fruit them invitro.&nbsp; In that case, add already moistened verm(with coffee) to your already hydrated grains and then sterilize.<br />RR","title":"Re: Adding verm to grain jars"}}